  "name": "Docetism",
  "localizedName": "Docetism",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A belief that Jesus didn’t have a human body and wasn’t fully a human being. It was based on a Greek idea. This idea was that bodies were evil. This idea was also that only spiritual things that last for ever were good. "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "textStyle"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Docetism became part of a way of thinking called Gnosticism. Gnosticism explained that the world had problems because people had bodies. Gnostics believed that human beings were saved by having secret knowledge."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
